# Codex AI Configuration – Optimized for Maximum Code Quality and Task Accuracy

# === Core Codex Instructions ===

**Codex and all engineers must follow these instructions for every code change. This is a non-negotiable baseline for quality.**

## Core Assumption
> You are contributing to a production system. Code must be fully complete, secure, accessible, and visually polished. All output must be deployable to `main` with no cleanup.

---

## Rules of Engagement

### 1. CODE PURITY
- Remove unused imports, placeholder elements, dead styles, and console logs.
- One source of truth only. Refactor the old — never clone or append.
- Output must be clean, minimal, and readable.

### 2. SELF-AUDIT CHECKLIST
- Validate responsiveness across all breakpoints.
- Run all tests (unit, snapshot, integration, accessibility).
- Zero build warnings or lint errors.
- Code is production-ready: `yarn build && preview` must pass.

### 3. UX POLISH
- Perfect spacing, alignment, rhythm, transitions.
- No layout jitter, overflow, or hardcoded pixel widths unless requested.
- Fully responsive from 320px → 1920px.

### 4. REACT + TAILWIND PROTOCOL
- Use flex/grid/flow. Avoid absolute/fixed unless specified.
- Use `gap`, `items-center`, `justify-*`, and responsive classes.
- Eliminate wrapper divs unless necessary.
- Modular components only. Co-locate logic/styles. Use `clsx` or `tailwind-variants`.

### 5. TESTING COVERAGE
- Use `screen.getByRole`, `findByText`, never brittle queries.
- Viewport simulation with `setViewport()` for mobile tests.
- Stub all APIs and side effects.
- Update DOM/snapshot tests when UI/layout changes.

### 6. SECURITY + ACCESSIBILITY (A11Y)
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, env vars, IPs, or external URLs.
- No third-party fonts/assets unless explicitly required.
- WCAG 2.1 AA required:
  - Contrast ≥ 4.5:1
  - Alt text
  - aria-* roles
  - Focus states
  - Keyboard nav

### 7. COMMUNICATION
- Don’t guess — clarify ambiguous requirements.
- Inline comments must explain intent (*why*, not *what*).
- Propose options with tradeoffs if spec is unclear.

---

## FINAL MERGE CHECKLIST
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Fully responsive
- [ ] A11y-verified
- [ ] Code linted + formatted
- [ ] No legacy or duplicate logic
- [ ] Semantic HTML
- [ ] Secure (no secrets, tokens, unsafe links)
- [ ] Visual polish complete

**Mindset**: You’re pushing to `main` on a Friday with no rollback window.

---

## [settings]

# Avoid unnecessary large/binary/compiled files
exclude = [
  "node_modules",
  "dist",
  "build",
  ".next",
  "out",
  "*.min.js",
  "*.map",
  "*.lock",
  "coverage",
  "*.log"
]

# .codex file for improved Codex performance

# Increase line length so Codex doesn’t truncate or misread JSX attributes
max_line_length = 240

# Clean up whitespace that can confuse parsing
trim_trailing_whitespace = true
preserve_blank_lines = false
collapse_whitespace = true

# General improvements to help Codex read long, dense files better
auto_format = true
detect_jsx = true
wrap_attributes = true
deduplicate_imports = true
remove_invalid_tags = true
preserve_class_order = false